    <string name="about_ncda_title">About NCDA</string>
    <string name="about_ncda_text">The National Council on Disability Affairs (NCDA) is the Philippine government\'s policy-making, coordinating, and monitoring body for disability issues.\nIt aims to promote the rights and well-being of persons with disabilities in the Philippines.\nYou can find more information on the official website: https://ncda.gov.ph/.</string>

    <string name="ncda_mission_title">Mission</string>
    <string name="ncda_mission_text">
        To provide direction to all stakeholders through policy formulation, coordination, monitoring, and evaluation of all activities to “MAKE THE RIGHTS REAL” for all.
    </string>

    <string name="ncda_vision_title">Vision</string>
    <string name="ncda_vision_text">
        All persons with disabilities are able to attain their fullest potential and to become active contributors and participants in nation-building.
    </string>

    <string name="ncda_core_values_title">NCDA Core Values</string>
    <string name="ncda_core_values_text">
        Community: A value that helps the NCDA be culturally unifying.\n
        Professionalism: A value that helps the NCDA fulfill its mission.\n
        Diversity and inclusion: A value that helps the NCDA fulfill its mission.\n
        Competency: A value that helps the NCDA fulfill its mission.\n
        Integrity: A value that helps the NCDA uphold honesty and ethical behavior.\n
        Inspiration: A value that helps the NCDA fulfill its mission.\n
        Innovation: An aspirational value that helps the NCDA fulfill its mission.\n
        Accountability: An aspirational value that helps the NCDA fulfill its mission.
    </string>

    <string name="ncda_services_title">NCDA Services</string>
    <string name="ncda_services_text">
        Policy development: The NCDA creates policies on disability prevention, rehabilitation, and equal opportunities for people with disabilities.\n
        Advocacy: The NCDA advocates for the rights of people with disabilities and proposes legislation.\n
        Public information: The NCDA develops public information programs on disability prevention, rehabilitation, and equal opportunities.\n
        Credentialing: The NCDA offers competency-based credentials for people in the field of career development.\n
        Program evaluation: The NCDA evaluates and monitors programs related to disability prevention and rehabilitation.
    </string>

